reviews.text:
It’s hard to separate the consistently late trains from the station itself, but it’s a well laid out station with easy access and surprisingly large parking for the size of the station.

Expect to wait for late trains.
Expect the ticket machine to only work 50% of the time
Expect to stand because there won’t be seats

But get there early and there will be parking. The station is secure and easy to get to on foot and good for those that need access.

No room during morning commute. 30% of the time there won't be room even to stand and you'll need to wait for the next train which is similarly packed. Extremely crowded, and only 2 - 3 carriage train even though consistently not enough room.
Besides commute, a lovely station with friendly part-time staff.
It's about time the line running through Woodlesford was electrified and the dirty diesel trains replaced with clean and quiet electric ones.
A basic railway station in West Yorkshire.
